SECTION 3 — RESTRICTIONS ON USE
================================================================================

3.1   Without the Author's prior explicit written permission, You must NOT:

      (a)  Deploy, execute, or host the Router Service or any portion thereof
           on any infrastructure for any purpose;

      (b)  Copy, clone, fork, or reproduce the Router Service in any medium;

      (c)  Distribute, sell, sublicense, or transfer the Router Service or any
           portion thereof to any third party;

      (d)  Modify the Router Service or create any Derivative Work, including
           reimplementing the Routing Intelligence in any other system;

      (e)  Reverse engineer, benchmark, or analyze the Routing Intelligence
           for the purpose of building a competing or similar routing system;

      (f)  Disclose, publish, or share the Routing Intelligence, Mesh Protocol
           specifications, or any other Confidential Information of the Author
           with any third party;

      (g)  Probe, scan, fuzz, or stress-test the Hosted Infrastructure through
           any means beyond normal user-initiated HTTP requests from the
           official PlanIt frontend;

      (h)  Attempt to forge, spoof, or bypass Mesh Protocol authentication;

      (i)  Use the Router Service's source code in any machine learning training
           dataset or AI model;

      (j)  Remove any copyright notices or proprietary markings from the
           Router Service;

      (k)  Use the Router Service for any Commercial Use without a separately
           executed commercial license agreement.

3.2   The Routing Intelligence specifically — including the backend scoring
      algorithm, health threshold values, boost mode parameters, and adaptive
      scaling heuristics — is classified as Confidential Information and a
      trade secret of the Author. Any attempt to extract, reproduce, or
      commercialize the Routing Intelligence in any form constitutes
      misappropriation of trade secrets in addition to a breach of this Agreement.

================================================================================
SECTION 4 — ROUTING INTELLIGENCE AS TRADE SECRET
================================================================================

4.1   The Author has invested substantial time, expertise, and iterative
      engineering effort in developing the Routing Intelligence. The specific
      combination of: health-check scoring weights; backend alive-state
      hysteresis logic; adaptive boost mode activation thresholds; the
      interaction between polling frequency and scoring decay; and the
      maintenance-safe exemption categorization — together constitute a
      proprietary system that is not publicly known or readily ascertainable
      and that provides the Author with a competitive advantage.

4.2   You agree to treat the Routing Intelligence as a trade secret of the
      Author, to use it only as permitted under Section 2.1 (reading for
      educational reference), and never to disclose it to any third party or
      use it as the basis for any other system.

4.3   Your obligation to maintain the confidentiality of the Routing
      Intelligence survives termination of this Agreement indefinitely,
      including beyond any applicable statute of limitations for copyright
      claims.

